caption: Vous voyez ce joli petit parc à côté de l' église Saint-Germain des prés, en sortant du métro.  La statue est Bernard Palissy(1510-1590)- Runaissance. French huguenot potter and writer, draughtsman and Painter. Famous for his rustic ceramics, often embellished with realistic elements (reptiles, shells, plants...), applied or modelled in high relief, which were widely imitated at the end of the 19thC.  You can find the work of this great artist at the Louvre Museum ;)  I live near by. It's a small park but my kid loves to play here.  It's honestly a bit sad that the park is dirty.... There are many cafe and street music goin on around the park. And don't forget to visit the church too!
Nice place to chill and relax - we actually came here twice as a resting stop away from the hustle and bustle.

Very pleasant little square with games for children, benches and above all, a magnificent view of the art nouveau portico made in the workshops of the Manufacture de Sèvres, coming from a pavilion of the Universal Exhibition of 1900 (architect Charles Risler, Jules Coutan (sculptor).  A must see

Quiet place and well maintained by the gardeners at certain times of the day we appreciate the serenity which reigns in this little corner of greenery, surrounded by very beautiful sculptures without forgetting the glass stele which recalls the memory of the Jewish children of the neighborhood murdered during the second World War.
Quiet location near the Saint-Germain-des-Prés church. You will find games for children there. Many benches in the shade. A beautiful art nouveau portico. Ideal for lunch or relaxation.

This small square is attached to the Saint-Germain-des-Prés church. You can see a statue of Bernard Palissy, a famous ceramist of the 16th century, and an enameled sandstone portico, Art Nouveau, a vestige of the Universal Exhibition of 1900. From the street, on the west side, on the wall, there is a "pastoral fountain" from 1925 by Félix-Alexandre Desruelles. Currently the square is closed for work.
Very nice little square. Ideal for relaxing
It was the porcelain or ceramic wall from Sèvres that made me want to enter this little square. Pleasant place next to the Saint Germain des Prés church in a nice area.
Play area from 2 years old Very happy to have found this place. Brand new equipment.
Very curious. You can't see it from the street. Well back in the square and go to the far right the vegetation la maquee un eu..
Pretty square in the heart of St Germain des Prés with attraction for young children
